07/12/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Two people suffered slight injuries in a bomb explosion in Istanbul late on Saturday (December 6th). The device exploded in a trash bin near a bank in the Fatih district. No one has claimed responsibility yet. 
In other news, Turkish warplanes bombed on Friday suspected positions of the Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in the Qandil Mountains of northern Iraq, the General Staff announced. The air strike was successful, the military said, without detailing whether the PKK suffered any casualties. (AFP, Haber 27, Hurriyet - 05/12/08, Anadolu news agency, NTV - 06/12/08)
